nem einzigartigen Praxisratgeber für den bibliothekarischen Alltag. Leseprobe öffnen  aThis book is a complete guide to the entire range of communication situations between library staff and users, including initial contact, the reference interview, training situations, conflict situations, complaints, and user orientation. Each chapter begins with a specific example that serves as the basis for the analysis of a problem situation. Extensive exercises are provided for independent study. Helpful tips, templates for drafting documents, and interview guidelines make this a uniquely practical guide to everyday library communication.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aPublic services (Libraries). 4aBibliothek. 4aKommunikationsfähigkeiten. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / General.2bisacsh  aCommunication Skills.  aLibrary.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Library Information Science 2000 - 2014z9783110636246oZDB-23-GLI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LIBRARY AND  INFORMATION SCIENCE  2012z9783110288933oZDB-23-DGB0 cprintz978311026897340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311026955040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110269550423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110269550/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LB  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGBb2012  aZDB-23-DGGb2012  aZDB-23-GLIc2000d2014